<item>
            <title>[OAK-1935] MAX_QUEUED_CONTINUATIONS feature not working in EventGenerator class</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1935</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1422&quot; title=&quot;Large number of queued EventGenerator.Continuation on big transactions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1422&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1422&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the  &lt;tt&gt;Continuation&lt;/tt&gt; created in &lt;tt&gt;fullQueue()&lt;/tt&gt; is put to the front of the List. This causes it to be taken right off the list again on the next call to &lt;tt&gt;generate()&lt;/tt&gt; instead of first continuing with the rest of the list allowing it to shrink. As a result the list may grow up to 2 x &lt;tt&gt;MAX_QUEUED_CONTINUATIONS&lt;/tt&gt; instead of 1 + &lt;tt&gt;MAX_QUEUED_CONTINUATIONS&lt;/tt&gt; as anticipated. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12724756">OAK-1935</key>
            <summary>MAX_QUEUED_CONTINUATIONS feature not working in EventGenerator class</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
