                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14048989" author="mduerig" created="Tue, 1 Jul 2014 15:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed at &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1607120&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1607120&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;New &lt;tt&gt;Continuation&lt;/tt&gt; instances go to the end of the queue now in the case the &lt;tt&gt;MAX_QUEUED_CONTINUATIONS&lt;/tt&gt; kicks in. This allows the queue to be cleared first until taking it up again where the current &lt;tt&gt;Continuation&lt;/tt&gt; left. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14159893" author="amitjain" created="Mon, 6 Oct 2014 04:09:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for 1.1.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
